abstract: The new BBC production of “King Lear” is great fun — and an uncomfortable reflection of American politics these days.
snippet: The new BBC production of “King Lear” is great fun — and an uncomfortable reflection of American politics these days.
lead_paragraph: I was going to watch the State of the Union speech the other week, honest I was, but I have this new policy of only screaming into my pillow once a day, so it didn’t pan out.

abstract: On one side of the debate, Bernie Sanders promises a single-payer revolution. On the other, Amy Klobuchar and Sherrod Brown are calling for incremental change.
snippet: On one side of the debate, Bernie Sanders promises a single-payer revolution. On the other, Amy Klobuchar and Sherrod Brown are calling for incremental change.
lead_paragraph: The debate unfolded over a period of days, on multiple televised stages in different states. There were no direct clashes between the candidates, no traces of personal animus — but a debate it was, the first vivid disputation over policy in the 2020 Democratic presidential primary.

headline_main: President Trump, Karl Lagerfeld, Bernie Sanders: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: An examination by The New York Times reveals the extent of President Trump’s assault on federal law enforcement, which has exposed him to accusations of obstruction of justice.
snippet: An examination by The New York Times reveals the extent of President Trump’s assault on federal law enforcement, which has exposed him to accusations of obstruction of justice.
lead_paragraph: Good Wednesday morning. Here are some of the stories making news in Washington and politics today.
headline_main: On Politics: Inside Trump’s War on the Investigations Encircling Him
